138bool
139dns__tsig_algvalid(unsigned int alg) {
140 return (alg == DST_ALG_HMACMD5 ||
141 alg == DST_ALG_HMACSHA1 ||
142 alg == DST_ALG_HMACSHA224 ||
143 alg == DST_ALG_HMACSHA256 ||
144 alg == DST_ALG_HMACSHA384 ||
145 alg == DST_ALG_HMACSHA512);
146}

148static void
149tsig_log(dns_tsigkey_t *key, int level, const char *fmt, ...) {
150 va_list ap;
151 char message[4096];
152 char namestr[DNS_NAME_FORMATSIZE];
153 char creatorstr[DNS_NAME_FORMATSIZE];
154
155 if (isc_log_wouldlog(dns_lctx, level) == false)
156 return;
157 if (key != NULL) {
158 dns_name_format(&key->name, namestr, sizeof(namestr));
159 } else {
160 strlcpy(namestr, "<null>", sizeof(namestr));
161 }
162
163 if (key != NULL && key->generated && key->creator) {
164 dns_name_format(key->creator, creatorstr, sizeof(creatorstr));
165 } else {
166 strlcpy(creatorstr, "<null>", sizeof(creatorstr));
167 }
168
169 va_start(ap, fmt);
170 vsnprintf(message, sizeof(message), fmt, ap);
171 va_end(ap);
172 if (key != NULL && key->generated) {
173 isc_log_write(dns_lctx,
174 DNS_LOGCATEGORY_DNSSEC, DNS_LOGMODULE_TSIG,
175 level, "tsig key '%s' (%s): %s",
176 namestr, creatorstr, message);
177 } else {
178 isc_log_write(dns_lctx,
179 DNS_LOGCATEGORY_DNSSEC, DNS_LOGMODULE_TSIG,
180 level, "tsig key '%s': %s", namestr, message);
181 }
182}

184static void
185remove_fromring(dns_tsigkey_t *tkey) {
186 if (tkey->generated) {
187 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(tkey->ring->lru, tkey, link);
188 tkey->ring->generated--;
189 }
190 (void)dns_rbt_deletename(tkey->ring->keys, &tkey->name, false);
191}
192
193static void
194adjust_lru(dns_tsigkey_t *tkey) {
195 if (tkey->generated) {
196 RWLOCK(&tkey->ring->lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
197 /*
198 * We may have been removed from the LRU list between
199 * removing the read lock and aquiring the write lock.
200 */
201 if (ISC_LINK_LINKED(tkey, link) &&
202 tkey->ring->lru.tail != tkey)
203 {
204 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(tkey->ring->lru, tkey, link);
205 ISC_LIST_APPEND(tkey->ring->lru, tkey, link);
206 }
207 RWUNLOCK(&tkey->ring->lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
208 }
209}

211/*
212 * A supplemental routine just to add a key to ring. Note that reference
213 * counter should be counted separately because we may be adding the key
214 * as part of creation of the key, in which case the reference counter was
215 * already initialized. Also note we don't need RWLOCK for the reference
216 * counter: it's protected by a separate lock.
217 */
218static isc_result_t
219keyring_add(dns_tsig_keyring_t *ring, const dns_name_t *name,
220 dns_tsigkey_t *tkey)
221{
222 isc_result_t result;
223
224 RWLOCK(&ring->lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
225 ring->writecount++;
226
227 /*
228 * Do on the fly cleaning. Find some nodes we might not
229 * want around any more.
230 */
231 if (ring->writecount > 10) {
232 cleanup_ring(ring);
233 ring->writecount = 0;
234 }
235
236 result = dns_rbt_addname(ring->keys, name, tkey);
237 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS && tkey->generated) {
238 /*
239 * Add the new key to the LRU list and remove the least
240 * recently used key if there are too many keys on the list.
241 */
242 ISC_LIST_APPEND(ring->lru, tkey, link);
243 if (ring->generated++ > ring->maxgenerated)
244 remove_fromring(ISC_LIST_HEAD(ring->lru));
245 }
246 RWUNLOCK(&ring->lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
247
248 return (result);
249}

251isc_result_t
252dns_tsigkey_createfromkey(const dns_name_t *name, const dns_name_t *algorithm,
253 dst_key_t *dstkey, bool generated,
254 const dns_name_t *creator, isc_stdtime_t inception,
255 isc_stdtime_t expire, isc_mem_t *mctx,
256 dns_tsig_keyring_t *ring, dns_tsigkey_t **key)
257{
258 dns_tsigkey_t *tkey;
259 isc_result_t ret;
260 unsigned int refs = 0;
261 unsigned int dstalg = 0;
262
263 REQUIRE(key == NULL || *key == NULL);
264 REQUIRE(name != NULL);
265 REQUIRE(algorithm != NULL);
266 REQUIRE(mctx != NULL);
267 REQUIRE(key != NULL || ring != NULL);
268
269 tkey = (dns_tsigkey_t *) isc_mem_get(mctx, sizeof(dns_tsigkey_t));
270 if (tkey == NULL)
271 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
272
273 dns_name_init(&tkey->name, NULL);
274 ret = dns_name_dup(name, mctx, &tkey->name);
275 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
276 goto cleanup_key;
277 (void)dns_name_downcase(&tkey->name, &tkey->name, NULL);
278
279 /* Check against known algorithm names */
280 dstalg = dns__tsig_algfromname(algorithm);
281 if (dstalg != 0) {
282 /*
283 * 'algorithm' must be set to a static pointer
284 * so that dns__tsig_algallocated() can compare them.
285 */
286 tkey->algorithm = dns__tsig_algnamefromname(algorithm);
287 if (dstkey != NULL && dst_key_alg(dstkey) != dstalg) {
288 ret = DNS_R_BADALG;
289 goto cleanup_name;
290 }
291 } else {
292 dns_name_t *tmpname;
293 if (dstkey != NULL) {
294 ret = DNS_R_BADALG;
295 goto cleanup_name;
296 }
297 tmpname = isc_mem_get(mctx, sizeof(dns_name_t));
298 if (tmpname == NULL) {
299 ret = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
300 goto cleanup_name;
301 }
302 dns_name_init(tmpname, NULL);
303 ret = dns_name_dup(algorithm, mctx, tmpname);
304 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
305 isc_mem_put(mctx, tmpname, sizeof(dns_name_t));
306 goto cleanup_name;
307 }
308 (void)dns_name_downcase(tmpname, tmpname, NULL);
309 tkey->algorithm = tmpname;
310 }
311
312 if (creator != NULL) {
313 tkey->creator = isc_mem_get(mctx, sizeof(dns_name_t));
314 if (tkey->creator == NULL) {
315 ret = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
316 goto cleanup_algorithm;
317 }
318 dns_name_init(tkey->creator, NULL);
319 ret = dns_name_dup(creator, mctx, tkey->creator);
320 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
321 isc_mem_put(mctx, tkey->creator, sizeof(dns_name_t));
322 goto cleanup_algorithm;
323 }
324 } else
325 tkey->creator = NULL;
326
327 tkey->key = NULL;
328 if (dstkey != NULL)
329 dst_key_attach(dstkey, &tkey->key);
330 tkey->ring = ring;
331
332 if (key != NULL)
333 refs = 1;
334 if (ring != NULL)
335 refs++;
336
337 isc_refcount_init(&tkey->refs, refs);
338
339 tkey->generated = generated;
340 tkey->inception = inception;
341 tkey->expire = expire;
342 tkey->mctx = NULL;
343 isc_mem_attach(mctx, &tkey->mctx);
344 ISC_LINK_INIT(tkey, link);
345
346 tkey->magic = TSIG_MAGIC;
347
348 if (ring != NULL) {
349 ret = keyring_add(ring, name, tkey);
350 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
351 goto cleanup_refs;
352 }
353
354 /*
355 * Ignore this if it's a GSS key, since the key size is meaningless.
356 */
357 if (dstkey != NULL && dst_key_size(dstkey) < 64 &&
358 dstalg != DST_ALG_GSSAPI) {
359 char namestr[DNS_NAME_FORMATSIZE];
360 dns_name_format(name, namestr, sizeof(namestr));
361 isc_log_write(dns_lctx, DNS_LOGCATEGORY_DNSSEC,
362 DNS_LOGMODULE_TSIG, ISC_LOG_INFO,
363 "the key '%s' is too short to be secure",
364 namestr);
365 }
366
367 if (key != NULL)
368 *key = tkey;
369
370 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
371
372 cleanup_refs:
373 tkey->magic = 0;
374 while (refs-- > 0) {
375 INSIST(isc_refcount_decrement(&tkey->refs) > 0);
376 }
377 isc_refcount_destroy(&tkey->refs);
378
379 if (tkey->key != NULL)
380 dst_key_free(&tkey->key);
381 if (tkey->creator != NULL) {
382 dns_name_free(tkey->creator, mctx);
383 isc_mem_put(mctx, tkey->creator, sizeof(dns_name_t));
384 }
385 cleanup_algorithm:
386 if (dns__tsig_algallocated(tkey->algorithm)) {
387 dns_name_t *tmpname;
388 DE_CONST(tkey->algorithm, tmpname);
389 if (dns_name_dynamic(tmpname))
390 dns_name_free(tmpname, mctx);
391 isc_mem_put(mctx, tmpname, sizeof(dns_name_t));
392 }
393 cleanup_name:
394 dns_name_free(&tkey->name, mctx);
395 cleanup_key:
396 isc_mem_put(mctx, tkey, sizeof(dns_tsigkey_t));
397
398 return (ret);
399}

401/*
402 * Find a few nodes to destroy if possible.
403 */
404static void
405cleanup_ring(dns_tsig_keyring_t *ring)
406{
407 isc_result_t result;
408 dns_rbtnodechain_t chain;
409 dns_name_t foundname;
410 dns_fixedname_t fixedorigin;
411 dns_name_t *origin;
412 isc_stdtime_t now;
413 dns_rbtnode_t *node;
414 dns_tsigkey_t *tkey;
415
416 /*
417 * Start up a new iterator each time.
418 */
419 isc_stdtime_get(&now);
420 dns_name_init(&foundname, NULL);
421 origin = dns_fixedname_initname(&fixedorigin);
422
423 again:
424 dns_rbtnodechain_init(&chain, ring->mctx);
425 result = dns_rbtnodechain_first(&chain, ring->keys, &foundname,
426 origin);
427 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS && result != DNS_R_NEWORIGIN) {
428 dns_rbtnodechain_invalidate(&chain);
429 return;
430 }
431
432 for (;;) {
433 node = NULL;
434 dns_rbtnodechain_current(&chain, &foundname, origin, &node);
435 tkey = node->data;
436 if (tkey != NULL) {
437 if (tkey->generated
438 && isc_refcount_current(&tkey->refs) == 1
439 && tkey->inception != tkey->expire
440 && tkey->expire < now) {
441 tsig_log(tkey, 2, "tsig expire: deleting");
442 /* delete the key */
443 dns_rbtnodechain_invalidate(&chain);
444 remove_fromring(tkey);
445 goto again;
446 }
447 }
448 result = dns_rbtnodechain_next(&chain, &foundname,
449 origin);
450 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS && result != DNS_R_NEWORIGIN) {
451 dns_rbtnodechain_invalidate(&chain);
452 return;
453 }
454 }
455}

462}

464/*
465 * Look up the DST_ALG_ constant for a given name.
466 */
467unsigned int
468dns__tsig_algfromname(const dns_name_t *algorithm) {
469 int i;
470 int n = sizeof(known_algs) / sizeof(*known_algs);
471 for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
472 const dns_name_t *name = known_algs[i].name;
473 if (algorithm == name || dns_name_equal(algorithm, name)) {
474 return (known_algs[i].dstalg);
475 }
476 }
477 return (0);
478}
479
480/*
481 * Convert an algorithm name into a pointer to the
482 * corresponding pre-defined dns_name_t structure.
483 */
484const dns_name_t*
485dns__tsig_algnamefromname(const dns_name_t *algorithm) {
486 int i;
487 int n = sizeof(known_algs) / sizeof(*known_algs);
488 for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
489 const dns_name_t *name = known_algs[i].name;
490 if (algorithm == name || dns_name_equal(algorithm, name)) {
491 return (name);
492 }
493 }
494 return (NULL);
495}
496
497/*
498 * Test whether the passed algorithm is NOT a pointer to one of the
499 * pre-defined known algorithms (and therefore one that has been
500 * dynamically allocated).
501 *
502 * This will return an incorrect result if passed a dynamically allocated
503 * dns_name_t that happens to match one of the pre-defined names.
504 */
505bool
506dns__tsig_algallocated(const dns_name_t *algorithm) {
507 int i;
508 int n = sizeof(known_algs) / sizeof(*known_algs);
509 for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
510 const dns_name_t *name = known_algs[i].name;
511 if (algorithm == name) {
512 return (false);
513 }
514 }
515 return (true);
516}

518static isc_result_t
519restore_key(dns_tsig_keyring_t *ring, isc_stdtime_t now, FILE *fp) {
520 dst_key_t *dstkey = NULL;
521 char namestr[1024];
522 char creatorstr[1024];
523 char algorithmstr[1024];
524 char keystr[4096];
525 unsigned int inception, expire;
526 int n;
527 isc_buffer_t b;
528 dns_name_t *name, *creator, *algorithm;
529 dns_fixedname_t fname, fcreator, falgorithm;
530 isc_result_t result;
531 unsigned int dstalg;
532
533 n = fscanf(fp, "%1023s %1023s %u %u %1023s %4095s\n", namestr,
534 creatorstr, &inception, &expire, algorithmstr, keystr);
535 if (n == EOF)
536 return (ISC_R_NOMORE);
537 if (n != 6)
538 return (ISC_R_FAILURE);
539
540 if (isc_serial_lt(expire, now))
541 return (DNS_R_EXPIRED);
542
543 name = dns_fixedname_initname(&fname);
544 isc_buffer_init(&b, namestr, strlen(namestr));
545 isc_buffer_add(&b, strlen(namestr));
546 result = dns_name_fromtext(name, &b, dns_rootname, 0, NULL);
547 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
548 return (result);
549
550 creator = dns_fixedname_initname(&fcreator);
551 isc_buffer_init(&b, creatorstr, strlen(creatorstr));
552 isc_buffer_add(&b, strlen(creatorstr));
553 result = dns_name_fromtext(creator, &b, dns_rootname, 0, NULL);
554 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
555 return (result);
556
557 algorithm = dns_fixedname_initname(&falgorithm);
558 isc_buffer_init(&b, algorithmstr, strlen(algorithmstr));
559 isc_buffer_add(&b, strlen(algorithmstr));
560 result = dns_name_fromtext(algorithm, &b, dns_rootname, 0, NULL);
561 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
562 return (result);
563
564 dstalg = dns__tsig_algfromname(algorithm);
565 if (dstalg == 0)
566 return (DNS_R_BADALG);
567
568 result = dst_key_restore(name, dstalg, DNS_KEYOWNER_ENTITY,
569 DNS_KEYPROTO_DNSSEC, dns_rdataclass_in,
570 ring->mctx, keystr, &dstkey);
571 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
572 return (result);
573
574 result = dns_tsigkey_createfromkey(name, algorithm, dstkey,
575 true, creator, inception,
576 expire, ring->mctx, ring, NULL);
577 if (dstkey != NULL)
578 dst_key_free(&dstkey);
579 return (result);
580}

582static void
583dump_key(dns_tsigkey_t *tkey, FILE *fp) {
584 char *buffer = NULL;
585 int length = 0;
586 char namestr[DNS_NAME_FORMATSIZE];
587 char creatorstr[DNS_NAME_FORMATSIZE];
588 char algorithmstr[DNS_NAME_FORMATSIZE];
589 isc_result_t result;
590
591 REQUIRE(tkey != NULL);
592 REQUIRE(fp != NULL);
593
594 dns_name_format(&tkey->name, namestr, sizeof(namestr));
595 dns_name_format(tkey->creator, creatorstr, sizeof(creatorstr));
596 dns_name_format(tkey->algorithm, algorithmstr, sizeof(algorithmstr));
597 result = dst_key_dump(tkey->key, tkey->mctx, &buffer, &length);
598 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
599 fprintf(fp, "%s %s %u %u %s %.*s\n", namestr, creatorstr,
600 tkey->inception, tkey->expire, algorithmstr,
601 length, buffer);
602 if (buffer != NULL)
603 isc_mem_put(tkey->mctx, buffer, length);
604}

606isc_result_t
607dns_tsigkeyring_dumpanddetach(dns_tsig_keyring_t **ringp, FILE *fp) {
608 isc_result_t result;
609 dns_rbtnodechain_t chain;
610 dns_name_t foundname;
611 dns_fixedname_t fixedorigin;
612 dns_name_t *origin;
613 isc_stdtime_t now;
614 dns_rbtnode_t *node;
615 dns_tsigkey_t *tkey;
616 dns_tsig_keyring_t *ring;
617 unsigned int references;
618
619 REQUIRE(ringp != NULL && *ringp != NULL);
620
621 ring = *ringp;
622 *ringp = NULL;
623
624 RWLOCK(&ring->lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
625 INSIST(ring->references > 0);
626 ring->references--;
627 references = ring->references;
628 RWUNLOCK(&ring->lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
629
630 if (references != 0)
631 return (DNS_R_CONTINUE);
632
633 isc_stdtime_get(&now);
634 dns_name_init(&foundname, NULL);
635 origin = dns_fixedname_initname(&fixedorigin);
636 dns_rbtnodechain_init(&chain, ring->mctx);
637 result = dns_rbtnodechain_first(&chain, ring->keys, &foundname,
638 origin);
639 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS && result != DNS_R_NEWORIGIN) {
640 dns_rbtnodechain_invalidate(&chain);
641 goto destroy;
642 }
643
644 for (;;) {
645 node = NULL;
646 dns_rbtnodechain_current(&chain, &foundname, origin, &node);
647 tkey = node->data;
648 if (tkey != NULL && tkey->generated && tkey->expire >= now)
649 dump_key(tkey, fp);
650 result = dns_rbtnodechain_next(&chain, &foundname,
651 origin);
652 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS && result != DNS_R_NEWORIGIN) {
653 dns_rbtnodechain_invalidate(&chain);
654 if (result == ISC_R_NOMORE)
655 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
656 goto destroy;
657 }
658 }
659
660 destroy:
661 destroyring(ring);
662 return (result);
663}

665isc_result_t
666dns_tsigkey_create(const dns_name_t *name, const dns_name_t *algorithm,
667 unsigned char *secret, int length, bool generated,
668 const dns_name_t *creator, isc_stdtime_t inception,
669 isc_stdtime_t expire, isc_mem_t *mctx,
670 dns_tsig_keyring_t *ring, dns_tsigkey_t **key)
671{
672 dst_key_t *dstkey = NULL;
673 isc_result_t result;
674 unsigned int dstalg = 0;
675
676 REQUIRE(length >= 0);
677 if (length > 0)
678 REQUIRE(secret != NULL);
679
680 dstalg = dns__tsig_algfromname(algorithm);
681 if (dns__tsig_algvalid(dstalg)) {
682 if (secret != NULL) {
683 isc_buffer_t b;
684
685 isc_buffer_init(&b, secret, length);
686 isc_buffer_add(&b, length);
687 result = dst_key_frombuffer(name, dstalg,
688 DNS_KEYOWNER_ENTITY,
689 DNS_KEYPROTO_DNSSEC,
690 dns_rdataclass_in,
691 &b, mctx, &dstkey);
692 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
693 return (result);
694 }
695 } else if (length > 0) {
696 return (DNS_R_BADALG);
697 }
698
699 result = dns_tsigkey_createfromkey(name, algorithm, dstkey,
700 generated, creator,
701 inception, expire, mctx, ring, key);
702 if (dstkey != NULL)
703 dst_key_free(&dstkey);
704 return (result);
705}

708dns_tsigkey_attach(dns_tsigkey_t *source, dns_tsigkey_t **targetp) {
709 REQUIRE(VALID_TSIG_KEY(source));
710 REQUIRE(targetp != NULL && *targetp == NULL);
711
712 isc_refcount_increment(&source->refs);
713 *targetp = source;
714}

716static void
717tsigkey_free(dns_tsigkey_t *key) {
718 REQUIRE(VALID_TSIG_KEY(key));
719
720 key->magic = 0;
721 dns_name_free(&key->name, key->mctx);
722 if (dns__tsig_algallocated(key->algorithm)) {
723 dns_name_t *name;
724 DE_CONST(key->algorithm, name);
725 dns_name_free(name, key->mctx);
726 isc_mem_put(key->mctx, name, sizeof(dns_name_t));
727 }
728 if (key->key != NULL)
729 dst_key_free(&key->key);
730 if (key->creator != NULL) {
731 dns_name_free(key->creator, key->mctx);
732 isc_mem_put(key->mctx, key->creator, sizeof(dns_name_t));
733 }
734 isc_mem_putanddetach(&key->mctx, key, sizeof(dns_tsigkey_t));
735}

738dns_tsigkey_detach(dns_tsigkey_t **keyp) {
739 REQUIRE(keyp != NULL && VALID_TSIG_KEY(*keyp));
740 dns_tsigkey_t *key = *keyp;
741 *keyp = NULL;
742
743 if (isc_refcount_decrement(&key->refs) == 1) {
744 isc_refcount_destroy(&key->refs);
745 tsigkey_free(key);
746 }
747}

758
759isc_result_t
760dns_tsig_sign(dns_message_t *msg) {
761 dns_tsigkey_t *key = NULL;
762 dns_rdata_any_tsig_t tsig, querytsig;
763 unsigned char data[128];
764 isc_buffer_t databuf, sigbuf;
765 isc_buffer_t *dynbuf = NULL;
766 dns_name_t *owner;
767 dns_rdata_t *rdata = NULL;
768 dns_rdatalist_t *datalist = NULL;
769 dns_rdataset_t *dataset = NULL;
770 isc_region_t r;
771 isc_stdtime_t now;
772 isc_mem_t *mctx;
773 dst_context_t *ctx = NULL;
774 isc_result_t ret;
775 unsigned char badtimedata[BADTIMELEN];
776 unsigned int sigsize = 0;
777 bool response;
778
779 REQUIRE(msg != NULL);
780 key = dns_message_gettsigkey(msg);
781 REQUIRE(VALID_TSIG_KEY(key));
782
783 /*
784 * If this is a response, there should be a TSIG in the query with the
785 * the exception if this is a TKEY request (see RFC 3645, Section 2.2).
786 */
787 response = is_response(msg);
788 if (response && msg->querytsig == NULL) {
789 if (msg->tkey != 1) {
790 return (DNS_R_EXPECTEDTSIG);
791 }
792 }
793
794 mctx = msg->mctx;
795
796 tsig.mctx = mctx;
797 tsig.common.rdclass = dns_rdataclass_any;
798 tsig.common.rdtype = dns_rdatatype_tsig;
799 ISC_LINK_INIT(&tsig.common, link);
800 dns_name_init(&tsig.algorithm, NULL);
801 dns_name_clone(key->algorithm, &tsig.algorithm);
802
803 isc_stdtime_get(&now);
804 tsig.timesigned = now + msg->timeadjust;
805 tsig.fudge = DNS_TSIG_FUDGE;
806
807 tsig.originalid = msg->id;
808
809 isc_buffer_init(&databuf, data, sizeof(data));
810
811 if (response)
812 tsig.error = msg->querytsigstatus;
813 else
814 tsig.error = dns_rcode_noerror;
815
816 if (tsig.error != dns_tsigerror_badtime) {
817 tsig.otherlen = 0;
818 tsig.other = NULL;
819 } else {
820 isc_buffer_t otherbuf;
821
822 tsig.otherlen = BADTIMELEN;
823 tsig.other = badtimedata;
824 isc_buffer_init(&otherbuf, tsig.other, tsig.otherlen);
825 isc_buffer_putuint48(&otherbuf, tsig.timesigned);
826 }
827
828 if ((key->key != NULL) &&
829 (tsig.error != dns_tsigerror_badsig) &&
830 (tsig.error != dns_tsigerror_badkey))
831 {
832 unsigned char header[DNS_MESSAGE_HEADERLEN];
833 isc_buffer_t headerbuf;
834 uint16_t digestbits;
835 bool querytsig_ok = false;
836
837 /*
838 * If it is a response, we assume that the request MAC
839 * has validated at this point. This is why we include a
840 * MAC length > 0 in the reply.
841 */
842 ret = dst_context_create(key->key, mctx,
843 DNS_LOGCATEGORY_DNSSEC,
844 true, 0, &ctx);
845 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
846 return (ret);
847
848 /*
849 * If this is a response, and if there was a TSIG in
850 * the query, digest the request's MAC.
851 *
852 * (Note: querytsig should be non-NULL for all
853 * responses except TKEY responses. Those may be signed
854 * with the newly-negotiated TSIG key even if the query
855 * wasn't signed.)
856 */
857 if (response && msg->querytsig != NULL) {
858 dns_rdata_t querytsigrdata = DNS_RDATA_INIT;
859
860 INSIST(msg->verified_sig);
861
862 ret = dns_rdataset_first(msg->querytsig);
863 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
864 goto cleanup_context;
865 dns_rdataset_current(msg->querytsig, &querytsigrdata);
866 ret = dns_rdata_tostruct(&querytsigrdata, &querytsig,
867 NULL);
868 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
869 goto cleanup_context;
870 isc_buffer_putuint16(&databuf, querytsig.siglen);
871 if (isc_buffer_availablelength(&databuf) <
872 querytsig.siglen) {
873 ret = ISC_R_NOSPACE;
874 goto cleanup_context;
875 }
876 isc_buffer_putmem(&databuf, querytsig.signature,
877 querytsig.siglen);
878 isc_buffer_usedregion(&databuf, &r);
879 ret = dst_context_adddata(ctx, &r);
880 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
881 goto cleanup_context;
882 querytsig_ok = true;
883 }
884
885 /*
886 * Digest the header.
887 */
888 isc_buffer_init(&headerbuf, header, sizeof(header));
889 dns_message_renderheader(msg, &headerbuf);
890 isc_buffer_usedregion(&headerbuf, &r);
891 ret = dst_context_adddata(ctx, &r);
892 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
893 goto cleanup_context;
894
895 /*
896 * Digest the remainder of the message.
897 */
898 isc_buffer_usedregion(msg->buffer, &r);
899 isc_region_consume(&r, DNS_MESSAGE_HEADERLEN);
900 ret = dst_context_adddata(ctx, &r);
901 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
902 goto cleanup_context;
903
904 if (msg->tcp_continuation == 0) {
905 /*
906 * Digest the name, class, ttl, alg.
907 */
908 dns_name_toregion(&key->name, &r);
909 ret = dst_context_adddata(ctx, &r);
910 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
911 goto cleanup_context;
912
913 isc_buffer_clear(&databuf);
914 isc_buffer_putuint16(&databuf, dns_rdataclass_any);
915 isc_buffer_putuint32(&databuf, 0); /* ttl */
916 isc_buffer_usedregion(&databuf, &r);
917 ret = dst_context_adddata(ctx, &r);
918 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
919 goto cleanup_context;
920
921 dns_name_toregion(&tsig.algorithm, &r);
922 ret = dst_context_adddata(ctx, &r);
923 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
924 goto cleanup_context;
925
926 }
927 /* Digest the timesigned and fudge */
928 isc_buffer_clear(&databuf);
929 if (tsig.error == dns_tsigerror_badtime && querytsig_ok) {
930 tsig.timesigned = querytsig.timesigned;
931 }
932 isc_buffer_putuint48(&databuf, tsig.timesigned);
933 isc_buffer_putuint16(&databuf, tsig.fudge);
934 isc_buffer_usedregion(&databuf, &r);
935 ret = dst_context_adddata(ctx, &r);
936 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
937 goto cleanup_context;
938
939 if (msg->tcp_continuation == 0) {
940 /*
941 * Digest the error and other data length.
942 */
943 isc_buffer_clear(&databuf);
944 isc_buffer_putuint16(&databuf, tsig.error);
945 isc_buffer_putuint16(&databuf, tsig.otherlen);
946
947 isc_buffer_usedregion(&databuf, &r);
948 ret = dst_context_adddata(ctx, &r);
949 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
950 goto cleanup_context;
951
952 /*
953 * Digest other data.
954 */
955 if (tsig.otherlen > 0) {
956 r.length = tsig.otherlen;
957 r.base = tsig.other;
958 ret = dst_context_adddata(ctx, &r);
959 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
960 goto cleanup_context;
961 }
962 }
963
964 ret = dst_key_sigsize(key->key, &sigsize);
965 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
966 goto cleanup_context;
967 tsig.signature = (unsigned char *) isc_mem_get(mctx, sigsize);
968 if (tsig.signature == NULL) {
969 ret = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
970 goto cleanup_context;
971 }
972
973 isc_buffer_init(&sigbuf, tsig.signature, sigsize);
974 ret = dst_context_sign(ctx, &sigbuf);
975 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
976 goto cleanup_signature;
977 dst_context_destroy(&ctx);
978 digestbits = dst_key_getbits(key->key);
979 if (digestbits != 0) {
980 unsigned int bytes = (digestbits + 7) / 8;
981 if (querytsig_ok && bytes < querytsig.siglen)
982 bytes = querytsig.siglen;
983 if (bytes > isc_buffer_usedlength(&sigbuf))
984 bytes = isc_buffer_usedlength(&sigbuf);
985 tsig.siglen = bytes;
986 } else
987 tsig.siglen = isc_buffer_usedlength(&sigbuf);
988 } else {
989 tsig.siglen = 0;
990 tsig.signature = NULL;
991 }
992
993 ret = dns_message_gettemprdata(msg, &rdata);
994 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
995 goto cleanup_signature;
996 ret = isc_buffer_allocate(msg->mctx, &dynbuf, 512);
997 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
998 goto cleanup_rdata;
999 ret = dns_rdata_fromstruct(rdata, dns_rdataclass_any,
1000 dns_rdatatype_tsig, &tsig, dynbuf);
1001 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1002 goto cleanup_dynbuf;
1003
1004 dns_message_takebuffer(msg, &dynbuf);
1005
1006 if (tsig.signature != NULL) {
1007 isc_mem_put(mctx, tsig.signature, sigsize);
1008 tsig.signature = NULL;
1009 }
1010
1011 owner = NULL;
1012 ret = dns_message_gettempname(msg, &owner);
1013 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1014 goto cleanup_rdata;
1015 dns_name_init(owner, NULL);
1016 ret = dns_name_dup(&key->name, msg->mctx, owner);
1017 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1018 goto cleanup_owner;
1019
1020 datalist = NULL;
1021 ret = dns_message_gettemprdatalist(msg, &datalist);
1022 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1023 goto cleanup_owner;
1024 dataset = NULL;
1025 ret = dns_message_gettemprdataset(msg, &dataset);
1026 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1027 goto cleanup_rdatalist;
1028 datalist->rdclass = dns_rdataclass_any;
1029 datalist->type = dns_rdatatype_tsig;
1030 ISC_LIST_APPEND(datalist->rdata, rdata, link);
1031 RUNTIME_CHECK(dns_rdatalist_tordataset(datalist, dataset)
1032 == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
1033 msg->tsig = dataset;
1034 msg->tsigname = owner;
1035
1036 /* Windows does not like the tsig name being compressed. */
1037 msg->tsigname->attributes |= DNS_NAMEATTR_NOCOMPRESS;
1038
1039 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
1040
1041 cleanup_rdatalist:
1042 dns_message_puttemprdatalist(msg, &datalist);
1043 cleanup_owner:
1044 dns_message_puttempname(msg, &owner);
1045 goto cleanup_rdata;
1046 cleanup_dynbuf:
1047 isc_buffer_free(&dynbuf);
1048 cleanup_rdata:
1049 dns_message_puttemprdata(msg, &rdata);
1050 cleanup_signature:
1051 if (tsig.signature != NULL)
1052 isc_mem_put(mctx, tsig.signature, sigsize);
1053 cleanup_context:
1054 if (ctx != NULL)
1055 dst_context_destroy(&ctx);
1056 return (ret);
1057}
1058
1059isc_result_t
1060dns_tsig_verify(isc_buffer_t *source, dns_message_t *msg,
1061 dns_tsig_keyring_t *ring1, dns_tsig_keyring_t *ring2)
1062{
1063 dns_rdata_any_tsig_t tsig, querytsig;
1064 isc_region_t r, source_r, header_r, sig_r;
1065 isc_buffer_t databuf;
1066 unsigned char data[32];
1067 dns_name_t *keyname;
1068 dns_rdata_t rdata = DNS_RDATA_INIT;
1069 isc_stdtime_t now;
1070 isc_result_t ret;
1071 dns_tsigkey_t *tsigkey;
1072 dst_key_t *key = NULL;
1073 unsigned char header[DNS_MESSAGE_HEADERLEN];
1074 dst_context_t *ctx = NULL;
1075 isc_mem_t *mctx;
1076 uint16_t addcount, id;
1077 unsigned int siglen;
1078 unsigned int alg;
1079 bool response;
1080
1081 REQUIRE(source != NULL);
1082 REQUIRE(DNS_MESSAGE_VALID(msg));
1083 tsigkey = dns_message_gettsigkey(msg);
1084 response = is_response(msg);
1085
1086 REQUIRE(tsigkey == NULL || VALID_TSIG_KEY(tsigkey));
1087
1088 msg->verify_attempted = 1;
1089 msg->verified_sig = 0;
1090 msg->tsigstatus = dns_tsigerror_badsig;
1091
1092 if (msg->tcp_continuation) {
1093 if (tsigkey == NULL || msg->querytsig == NULL)
1094 return (DNS_R_UNEXPECTEDTSIG);
1095 return (tsig_verify_tcp(source, msg));
1096 }
1097
1098 /*
1099 * There should be a TSIG record...
1100 */
1101 if (msg->tsig == NULL)
1102 return (DNS_R_EXPECTEDTSIG);
1103
1104 /*
1105 * If this is a response and there's no key or query TSIG, there
1106 * shouldn't be one on the response.
1107 */
1108 if (response && (tsigkey == NULL || msg->querytsig == NULL))
1109 return (DNS_R_UNEXPECTEDTSIG);
1110
1111 mctx = msg->mctx;
1112
1113 /*
1114 * If we're here, we know the message is well formed and contains a
1115 * TSIG record.
1116 */
1117
1118 keyname = msg->tsigname;
1119 ret = dns_rdataset_first(msg->tsig);
1120 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1121 return (ret);
1122 dns_rdataset_current(msg->tsig, &rdata);
1123 ret = dns_rdata_tostruct(&rdata, &tsig, NULL);
1124 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1125 return (ret);
1126 dns_rdata_reset(&rdata);
1127 if (response) {
1128 ret = dns_rdataset_first(msg->querytsig);
1129 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1130 return (ret);
1131 dns_rdataset_current(msg->querytsig, &rdata);
1132 ret = dns_rdata_tostruct(&rdata, &querytsig, NULL);
1133 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1134 return (ret);
1135 }
1136#if defined(__clang__) && \
1137 ( __clang_major__ < 3 || \
1138 (__clang_major__ == 3 && __clang_minor__ < 2) || \
1139 (__clang_major__ == 4 && __clang_minor__ < 2))
1140 /* false positive: http://llvm.org/bugs/show_bug.cgi?id=14461 */
1141 else memset(&querytsig, 0, sizeof(querytsig));
1142#endif
1143
1144 /*
1145 * Do the key name and algorithm match that of the query?
1146 */
1147 if (response &&
1148 (!dns_name_equal(keyname, &tsigkey->name) ||
1149 !dns_name_equal(&tsig.algorithm, &querytsig.algorithm))) {
1150 msg->tsigstatus = dns_tsigerror_badkey;
1151 tsig_log(msg->tsigkey, 2,
1152 "key name and algorithm do not match");
1153 return (DNS_R_TSIGVERIFYFAILURE);
1154 }
1155
1156 /*
1157 * Get the current time.
1158 */
1159 isc_stdtime_get(&now);
1160
1161 /*
1162 * Find dns_tsigkey_t based on keyname.
1163 */
1164 if (tsigkey == NULL) {
1165 ret = ISC_R_NOTFOUND;
1166 if (ring1 != NULL)
1167 ret = dns_tsigkey_find(&tsigkey, keyname,
1168 &tsig.algorithm, ring1);
1169 if (ret == ISC_R_NOTFOUND && ring2 != NULL)
1170 ret = dns_tsigkey_find(&tsigkey, keyname,
1171 &tsig.algorithm, ring2);
1172 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1173 msg->tsigstatus = dns_tsigerror_badkey;
1174 ret = dns_tsigkey_create(keyname, &tsig.algorithm,
1175 NULL, 0, false, NULL,
1176 now, now,
1177 mctx, NULL, &msg->tsigkey);
1178 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1179 return (ret);
1180 tsig_log(msg->tsigkey, 2, "unknown key");
1181 return (DNS_R_TSIGVERIFYFAILURE);
1182 }
1183 msg->tsigkey = tsigkey;
1184 }
1185
1186 key = tsigkey->key;
1187
1188 /*
1189 * Check digest length.
1190 */
1191 alg = dst_key_alg(key);
1192 ret = dst_key_sigsize(key, &siglen);
1193 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1194 return (ret);
1195 if (dns__tsig_algvalid(alg)) {
1196 if (tsig.siglen > siglen) {
1197 tsig_log(msg->tsigkey, 2, "signature length too big");
1198 return (DNS_R_FORMERR);
1199 }
1200 if (tsig.siglen > 0 &&
1201 (tsig.siglen < 10 || tsig.siglen < ((siglen + 1) / 2)))
1202 {
1203 tsig_log(msg->tsigkey, 2,
1204 "signature length below minimum");
1205 return (DNS_R_FORMERR);
1206 }
1207 }
1208
1209 if (tsig.siglen > 0) {
1210 uint16_t addcount_n;
1211
1212 sig_r.base = tsig.signature;
1213 sig_r.length = tsig.siglen;
1214
1215 ret = dst_context_create(key, mctx,
1216 DNS_LOGCATEGORY_DNSSEC,
1217 false, 0, &ctx);
1218 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1219 return (ret);
1220
1221 if (response) {
1222 isc_buffer_init(&databuf, data, sizeof(data));
1223 isc_buffer_putuint16(&databuf, querytsig.siglen);
1224 isc_buffer_usedregion(&databuf, &r);
1225 ret = dst_context_adddata(ctx, &r);
1226 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1227 goto cleanup_context;
1228 if (querytsig.siglen > 0) {
1229 r.length = querytsig.siglen;
1230 r.base = querytsig.signature;
1231 ret = dst_context_adddata(ctx, &r);
1232 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1233 goto cleanup_context;
1234 }
1235 }
1236
1237 /*
1238 * Extract the header.
1239 */
1240 isc_buffer_usedregion(source, &r);
1241 memmove(header, r.base, DNS_MESSAGE_HEADERLEN);
1242 isc_region_consume(&r, DNS_MESSAGE_HEADERLEN);
1243
1244 /*
1245 * Decrement the additional field counter.
1246 */
1247 memmove(&addcount, &header[DNS_MESSAGE_HEADERLEN - 2], 2);
1248 addcount_n = ntohs(addcount);
1249 addcount = htons((uint16_t)(addcount_n - 1));
1250 memmove(&header[DNS_MESSAGE_HEADERLEN - 2], &addcount, 2);
1251
1252 /*
1253 * Put in the original id.
1254 */
1255 id = htons(tsig.originalid);
1256 memmove(&header[0], &id, 2);
1257
1258 /*
1259 * Digest the modified header.
1260 */
1261 header_r.base = (unsigned char *) header;
1262 header_r.length = DNS_MESSAGE_HEADERLEN;
1263 ret = dst_context_adddata(ctx, &header_r);
1264 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1265 goto cleanup_context;
1266
1267 /*
1268 * Digest all non-TSIG records.
1269 */
1270 isc_buffer_usedregion(source, &source_r);
1271 r.base = source_r.base + DNS_MESSAGE_HEADERLEN;
1272 r.length = msg->sigstart - DNS_MESSAGE_HEADERLEN;
1273 ret = dst_context_adddata(ctx, &r);
1274 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1275 goto cleanup_context;
1276
1277 /*
1278 * Digest the key name.
1279 */
1280 dns_name_toregion(&tsigkey->name, &r);
1281 ret = dst_context_adddata(ctx, &r);
1282 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1283 goto cleanup_context;
1284
1285 isc_buffer_init(&databuf, data, sizeof(data));
1286 isc_buffer_putuint16(&databuf, tsig.common.rdclass);
1287 isc_buffer_putuint32(&databuf, msg->tsig->ttl);
1288 isc_buffer_usedregion(&databuf, &r);
1289 ret = dst_context_adddata(ctx, &r);
1290 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1291 goto cleanup_context;
1292
1293 /*
1294 * Digest the key algorithm.
1295 */
1296 dns_name_toregion(tsigkey->algorithm, &r);
1297 ret = dst_context_adddata(ctx, &r);
1298 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1299 goto cleanup_context;
1300
1301 isc_buffer_clear(&databuf);
1302 isc_buffer_putuint48(&databuf, tsig.timesigned);
1303 isc_buffer_putuint16(&databuf, tsig.fudge);
1304 isc_buffer_putuint16(&databuf, tsig.error);
1305 isc_buffer_putuint16(&databuf, tsig.otherlen);
1306 isc_buffer_usedregion(&databuf, &r);
1307 ret = dst_context_adddata(ctx, &r);
1308 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1309 goto cleanup_context;
1310
1311 if (tsig.otherlen > 0) {
1312 r.base = tsig.other;
1313 r.length = tsig.otherlen;
1314 ret = dst_context_adddata(ctx, &r);
1315 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1316 goto cleanup_context;
1317 }
1318
1319 ret = dst_context_verify(ctx, &sig_r);
1320 if (ret == DST_R_VERIFYFAILURE) {
1321 ret = DNS_R_TSIGVERIFYFAILURE;
1322 tsig_log(msg->tsigkey, 2,
1323 "signature failed to verify(1)");
1324 goto cleanup_context;
1325 } else if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1326 goto cleanup_context;
1327 }
1328 msg->verified_sig = 1;
1329 } else if (tsig.error != dns_tsigerror_badsig &&
1330 tsig.error != dns_tsigerror_badkey) {
1331 tsig_log(msg->tsigkey, 2, "signature was empty");
1332 return (DNS_R_TSIGVERIFYFAILURE);
1333 }
1334
1335 /*
1336 * Here at this point, the MAC has been verified. Even if any of
1337 * the following code returns a TSIG error, the reply will be
1338 * signed and WILL always include the request MAC in the digest
1339 * computation.
1340 */
1341
1342 /*
1343 * Is the time ok?
1344 */
1345 if (now + msg->timeadjust > tsig.timesigned + tsig.fudge) {
1346 msg->tsigstatus = dns_tsigerror_badtime;
1347 tsig_log(msg->tsigkey, 2, "signature has expired");
1348 ret = DNS_R_CLOCKSKEW;
1349 goto cleanup_context;
1350 } else if (now + msg->timeadjust < tsig.timesigned - tsig.fudge) {
1351 msg->tsigstatus = dns_tsigerror_badtime;
1352 tsig_log(msg->tsigkey, 2, "signature is in the future");
1353 ret = DNS_R_CLOCKSKEW;
1354 goto cleanup_context;
1355 }
1356
1357 if (dns__tsig_algvalid(alg)) {
1358 uint16_t digestbits = dst_key_getbits(key);
1359
1360 if (tsig.siglen > 0 && digestbits != 0 &&
1361 tsig.siglen < ((digestbits + 7) / 8))
1362 {
1363 msg->tsigstatus = dns_tsigerror_badtrunc;
1364 tsig_log(msg->tsigkey, 2,
1365 "truncated signature length too small");
1366 ret = DNS_R_TSIGVERIFYFAILURE;
1367 goto cleanup_context;
1368 }
1369 if (tsig.siglen > 0 && digestbits == 0 &&
1370 tsig.siglen < siglen)
1371 {
1372 msg->tsigstatus = dns_tsigerror_badtrunc;
1373 tsig_log(msg->tsigkey, 2, "signature length too small");
1374 ret = DNS_R_TSIGVERIFYFAILURE;
1375 goto cleanup_context;
1376 }
1377 }
1378
1379 if (tsig.error != dns_rcode_noerror) {
1380 msg->tsigstatus = tsig.error;
1381 if (tsig.error == dns_tsigerror_badtime)
1382 ret = DNS_R_CLOCKSKEW;
1383 else
1384 ret = DNS_R_TSIGERRORSET;
1385 goto cleanup_context;
1386 }
1387
1388 msg->tsigstatus = dns_rcode_noerror;
1389 ret = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
1390
1391 cleanup_context:
1392 if (ctx != NULL)
1393 dst_context_destroy(&ctx);
1394
1395 return (ret);
1396}

1398static isc_result_t
1399tsig_verify_tcp(isc_buffer_t *source, dns_message_t *msg) {
1400 dns_rdata_any_tsig_t tsig, querytsig;
1401 isc_region_t r, source_r, header_r, sig_r;
1402 isc_buffer_t databuf;
1403 unsigned char data[32];
1404 dns_name_t *keyname;
1405 dns_rdata_t rdata = DNS_RDATA_INIT;
1406 isc_stdtime_t now;
1407 isc_result_t ret;
1408 dns_tsigkey_t *tsigkey;
1409 dst_key_t *key = NULL;
1410 unsigned char header[DNS_MESSAGE_HEADERLEN];
1411 uint16_t addcount, id;
1412 bool has_tsig = false;
1413 isc_mem_t *mctx;
1414 unsigned int siglen;
1415 unsigned int alg;
1416
1417 REQUIRE(source != NULL);
1418 REQUIRE(msg != NULL);
1419 REQUIRE(dns_message_gettsigkey(msg) != NULL);
1420 REQUIRE(msg->tcp_continuation == 1);
1421 REQUIRE(msg->querytsig != NULL);
1422
1423 msg->verified_sig = 0;
1424 msg->tsigstatus = dns_tsigerror_badsig;
1425
1426 if (!is_response(msg))
1427 return (DNS_R_EXPECTEDRESPONSE);
1428
1429 mctx = msg->mctx;
1430
1431 tsigkey = dns_message_gettsigkey(msg);
1432 key = tsigkey->key;
1433
1434 /*
1435 * Extract and parse the previous TSIG
1436 */
1437 ret = dns_rdataset_first(msg->querytsig);
1438 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1439 return (ret);
1440 dns_rdataset_current(msg->querytsig, &rdata);
1441 ret = dns_rdata_tostruct(&rdata, &querytsig, NULL);
1442 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1443 return (ret);
1444 dns_rdata_reset(&rdata);
1445
1446 /*
1447 * If there is a TSIG in this message, do some checks.
1448 */
1449 if (msg->tsig != NULL) {
1450 has_tsig = true;
1451
1452 keyname = msg->tsigname;
1453 ret = dns_rdataset_first(msg->tsig);
1454 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1455 goto cleanup_querystruct;
1456 dns_rdataset_current(msg->tsig, &rdata);
1457 ret = dns_rdata_tostruct(&rdata, &tsig, NULL);
1458 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1459 goto cleanup_querystruct;
1460
1461 /*
1462 * Do the key name and algorithm match that of the query?
1463 */
1464 if (!dns_name_equal(keyname, &tsigkey->name) ||
1465 !dns_name_equal(&tsig.algorithm, &querytsig.algorithm))
1466 {
1467 msg->tsigstatus = dns_tsigerror_badkey;
1468 ret = DNS_R_TSIGVERIFYFAILURE;
1469 tsig_log(msg->tsigkey, 2,
1470 "key name and algorithm do not match");
1471 goto cleanup_querystruct;
1472 }
1473
1474 /*
1475 * Check digest length.
1476 */
1477 alg = dst_key_alg(key);
1478 ret = dst_key_sigsize(key, &siglen);
1479 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1480 goto cleanup_querystruct;
1481 if (dns__tsig_algvalid(alg)) {
1482 if (tsig.siglen > siglen) {
1483 tsig_log(tsigkey, 2,
1484 "signature length too big");
1485 ret = DNS_R_FORMERR;
1486 goto cleanup_querystruct;
1487 }
1488 if (tsig.siglen > 0 &&
1489 (tsig.siglen < 10 ||
1490 tsig.siglen < ((siglen + 1) / 2)))
1491 {
1492 tsig_log(tsigkey, 2,
1493 "signature length below minimum");
1494 ret = DNS_R_FORMERR;
1495 goto cleanup_querystruct;
1496 }
1497 }
1498 }
1499
1500 if (msg->tsigctx == NULL) {
1501 ret = dst_context_create(key, mctx,
1502 DNS_LOGCATEGORY_DNSSEC,
1503 false, 0, &msg->tsigctx);
1504 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1505 goto cleanup_querystruct;
1506
1507 /*
1508 * Digest the length of the query signature
1509 */
1510 isc_buffer_init(&databuf, data, sizeof(data));
1511 isc_buffer_putuint16(&databuf, querytsig.siglen);
1512 isc_buffer_usedregion(&databuf, &r);
1513 ret = dst_context_adddata(msg->tsigctx, &r);
1514 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1515 goto cleanup_context;
1516
1517 /*
1518 * Digest the data of the query signature
1519 */
1520 if (querytsig.siglen > 0) {
1521 r.length = querytsig.siglen;
1522 r.base = querytsig.signature;
1523 ret = dst_context_adddata(msg->tsigctx, &r);
1524 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1525 goto cleanup_context;
1526 }
1527 }
1528
1529 /*
1530 * Extract the header.
1531 */
1532 isc_buffer_usedregion(source, &r);
1533 memmove(header, r.base, DNS_MESSAGE_HEADERLEN);
1534 isc_region_consume(&r, DNS_MESSAGE_HEADERLEN);
1535
1536 /*
1537 * Decrement the additional field counter if necessary.
1538 */
1539 if (has_tsig) {
1540 uint16_t addcount_n;
1541
1542 memmove(&addcount, &header[DNS_MESSAGE_HEADERLEN - 2], 2);
1543 addcount_n = ntohs(addcount);
1544 addcount = htons((uint16_t)(addcount_n - 1));
1545 memmove(&header[DNS_MESSAGE_HEADERLEN - 2], &addcount, 2);
1546
1547 /*
1548 * Put in the original id.
1549 *
1550 * XXX Can TCP transfers be forwarded? How would that
1551 * work?
1552 */
1553 id = htons(tsig.originalid);
1554 memmove(&header[0], &id, 2);
1555 }
1556
1557 /*
1558 * Digest the modified header.
1559 */
1560 header_r.base = (unsigned char *) header;
1561 header_r.length = DNS_MESSAGE_HEADERLEN;
1562 ret = dst_context_adddata(msg->tsigctx, &header_r);
1563 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1564 goto cleanup_context;
1565
1566 /*
1567 * Digest all non-TSIG records.
1568 */
1569 isc_buffer_usedregion(source, &source_r);
1570 r.base = source_r.base + DNS_MESSAGE_HEADERLEN;
1571 if (has_tsig)
1572 r.length = msg->sigstart - DNS_MESSAGE_HEADERLEN;
1573 else
1574 r.length = source_r.length - DNS_MESSAGE_HEADERLEN;
1575 ret = dst_context_adddata(msg->tsigctx, &r);
1576 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1577 goto cleanup_context;
1578
1579 /*
1580 * Digest the time signed and fudge.
1581 */
1582 if (has_tsig) {
1583 isc_buffer_init(&databuf, data, sizeof(data));
1584 isc_buffer_putuint48(&databuf, tsig.timesigned);
1585 isc_buffer_putuint16(&databuf, tsig.fudge);
1586 isc_buffer_usedregion(&databuf, &r);
1587 ret = dst_context_adddata(msg->tsigctx, &r);
1588 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1589 goto cleanup_context;
1590
1591 sig_r.base = tsig.signature;
1592 sig_r.length = tsig.siglen;
1593 if (tsig.siglen == 0) {
1594 if (tsig.error != dns_rcode_noerror) {
1595 msg->tsigstatus = tsig.error;
1596 if (tsig.error == dns_tsigerror_badtime) {
1597 ret = DNS_R_CLOCKSKEW;
1598 } else {
1599 ret = DNS_R_TSIGERRORSET;
1600 }
1601 } else {
1602 tsig_log(msg->tsigkey, 2,
1603 "signature is empty");
1604 ret = DNS_R_TSIGVERIFYFAILURE;
1605 }
1606 goto cleanup_context;
1607 }
1608
1609 ret = dst_context_verify(msg->tsigctx, &sig_r);
1610 if (ret == DST_R_VERIFYFAILURE) {
1611 tsig_log(msg->tsigkey, 2,
1612 "signature failed to verify(2)");
1613 ret = DNS_R_TSIGVERIFYFAILURE;
1614 goto cleanup_context;
1615 } else if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1616 goto cleanup_context;
1617 }
1618 msg->verified_sig = 1;
1619
1620 /*
1621 * Here at this point, the MAC has been verified. Even
1622 * if any of the following code returns a TSIG error,
1623 * the reply will be signed and WILL always include the
1624 * request MAC in the digest computation.
1625 */
1626
1627 /*
1628 * Is the time ok?
1629 */
1630 isc_stdtime_get(&now);
1631
1632 if (now + msg->timeadjust > tsig.timesigned + tsig.fudge) {
1633 msg->tsigstatus = dns_tsigerror_badtime;
1634 tsig_log(msg->tsigkey, 2, "signature has expired");
1635 ret = DNS_R_CLOCKSKEW;
1636 goto cleanup_context;
1637 } else if (now + msg->timeadjust <
1638 tsig.timesigned - tsig.fudge)
1639 {
1640 msg->tsigstatus = dns_tsigerror_badtime;
1641 tsig_log(msg->tsigkey, 2,
1642 "signature is in the future");
1643 ret = DNS_R_CLOCKSKEW;
1644 goto cleanup_context;
1645 }
1646
1647 alg = dst_key_alg(key);
1648 ret = dst_key_sigsize(key, &siglen);
1649 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1650 goto cleanup_context;
1651 if (dns__tsig_algvalid(alg)) {
1652 uint16_t digestbits = dst_key_getbits(key);
1653
1654 if (tsig.siglen > 0 && digestbits != 0 &&
1655 tsig.siglen < ((digestbits + 7) / 8))
1656 {
1657 msg->tsigstatus = dns_tsigerror_badtrunc;
1658 tsig_log(msg->tsigkey, 2,
1659 "truncated signature length "
1660 "too small");
1661 ret = DNS_R_TSIGVERIFYFAILURE;
1662 goto cleanup_context;
1663 }
1664 if (tsig.siglen > 0 && digestbits == 0 &&
1665 tsig.siglen < siglen)
1666 {
1667 msg->tsigstatus = dns_tsigerror_badtrunc;
1668 tsig_log(msg->tsigkey, 2,
1669 "signature length too small");
1670 ret = DNS_R_TSIGVERIFYFAILURE;
1671 goto cleanup_context;
1672 }
1673 }
1674
1675 if (tsig.error != dns_rcode_noerror) {
1676 msg->tsigstatus = tsig.error;
1677 if (tsig.error == dns_tsigerror_badtime)
1678 ret = DNS_R_CLOCKSKEW;
1679 else
1680 ret = DNS_R_TSIGERRORSET;
1681 goto cleanup_context;
1682 }
1683 }
1684
1685 msg->tsigstatus = dns_rcode_noerror;
1686 ret = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
1687
1688 cleanup_context:
1689 /*
1690 * Except in error conditions, don't destroy the DST context
1691 * for unsigned messages; it is a running sum till the next
1692 * TSIG signed message.
1693 */
1694 if ((ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS || has_tsig) && msg->tsigctx != NULL) {
1695 dst_context_destroy(&msg->tsigctx);
1696 }
1697
1698 cleanup_querystruct:
1699 dns_rdata_freestruct(&querytsig);
1700
1701 return (ret);
1702}

1704isc_result_t
1705dns_tsigkey_find(dns_tsigkey_t **tsigkey, const dns_name_t *name,
1706 const dns_name_t *algorithm, dns_tsig_keyring_t *ring)
1707{
1708 dns_tsigkey_t *key;
1709 isc_stdtime_t now;
1710 isc_result_t result;
1711
1712 REQUIRE(tsigkey != NULL);
1713 REQUIRE(*tsigkey == NULL);
1714 REQUIRE(name != NULL);
1715 REQUIRE(ring != NULL);
1716
1717 RWLOCK(&ring->lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
1718 cleanup_ring(ring);
1719 RWUNLOCK(&ring->lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
1720
1721 isc_stdtime_get(&now);
1722 RWLOCK(&ring->lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
1723 key = NULL;
1724 result = dns_rbt_findname(ring->keys, name, 0, NULL, (void *)&key);
1725 if (result == DNS_R_PARTIALMATCH || result == ISC_R_NOTFOUND) {
1726 RWUNLOCK(&ring->lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
1727 return (ISC_R_NOTFOUND);
1728 }
1729 if (algorithm != NULL && !dns_name_equal(key->algorithm, algorithm)) {
1730 RWUNLOCK(&ring->lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
1731 return (ISC_R_NOTFOUND);
1732 }
1733 if (key->inception != key->expire && isc_serial_lt(key->expire, now)) {
1734 /*
1735 * The key has expired.
1736 */
1737 RWUNLOCK(&ring->lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
1738 RWLOCK(&ring->lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
1739 remove_fromring(key);
1740 RWUNLOCK(&ring->lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
1741 return (ISC_R_NOTFOUND);
1742 }
1743#if 0
1744 /*
1745 * MPAXXX We really should look at the inception time.
1746 */
1747 if (key->inception != key->expire &&
1748 isc_serial_lt(key->inception, now)) {
1749 RWUNLOCK(&ring->lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
1750 adjust_lru(key);
1751 return (ISC_R_NOTFOUND);
1752 }
1753#endif
1754 isc_refcount_increment(&key->refs);
1755 RWUNLOCK(&ring->lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
1756 adjust_lru(key);
1757 *tsigkey = key;
1758 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
1759}

1763 dns_tsigkey_t *key;
1764
1765 REQUIRE(node != NULL);
1766
1767 UNUSED(_unused);

1777isc_result_t
1778dns_tsigkeyring_create(isc_mem_t *mctx, dns_tsig_keyring_t **ringp) {
1779 isc_result_t result;
1780 dns_tsig_keyring_t *ring;
1781
1782 REQUIRE(mctx != NULL);
1783 REQUIRE(ringp != NULL);
1784 REQUIRE(*ringp == NULL);
1785
1786 ring = isc_mem_get(mctx, sizeof(dns_tsig_keyring_t));
1787 if (ring == NULL)
1788 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
1789
1790 result = isc_rwlock_init(&ring->lock, 0, 0);
1791 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1792 isc_mem_put(mctx, ring, sizeof(dns_tsig_keyring_t));
1793 return (result);
1794 }
1795
1796 ring->keys = NULL;
1797 result = dns_rbt_create(mctx, free_tsignode, NULL, &ring->keys);
1798 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1799 isc_rwlock_destroy(&ring->lock);
1800 isc_mem_put(mctx, ring, sizeof(dns_tsig_keyring_t));
1801 return (result);
1802 }
1803
1804 ring->writecount = 0;
1805 ring->mctx = NULL;
1806 ring->generated = 0;
1807 ring->maxgenerated = DNS_TSIG_MAXGENERATEDKEYS;
1808 ISC_LIST_INIT(ring->lru);
1809 isc_mem_attach(mctx, &ring->mctx);
1810 ring->references = 1;
1811
1812 *ringp = ring;
1813 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
1814}

1829void
1830dns_tsigkeyring_attach(dns_tsig_keyring_t *source, dns_tsig_keyring_t **target)
1831{
1832 REQUIRE(source != NULL);
1833 REQUIRE(target != NULL && *target == NULL);
1834
1835 RWLOCK(&source->lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
1836 INSIST(source->references > 0);
1837 source->references++;
1838 INSIST(source->references > 0);
1839 *target = source;
1840 RWUNLOCK(&source->lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
1841}

1843void
1844dns_tsigkeyring_detach(dns_tsig_keyring_t **ringp) {
1845 dns_tsig_keyring_t *ring;
1846 unsigned int references;
1847
1848 REQUIRE(ringp != NULL);
1849 REQUIRE(*ringp != NULL);
1850
1851 ring = *ringp;
1852 *ringp = NULL;
1853
1854 RWLOCK(&ring->lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
1855 INSIST(ring->references > 0);
1856 ring->references--;
1857 references = ring->references;
1858 RWUNLOCK(&ring->lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
1859
1860 if (references == 0)
1861 destroyring(ring);
1862}

1869 isc_stdtime_get(&now);
1870 do {
